(d) becomes known to Receiver on a non-confidential basis from a source other than VIDAR without breach of this Agreement by Receiver;

(e) is disclosed to a third party by VIDAR without restrictions against non-disclosure similar to those contained in this Agreement;

(f)  is disclosed pursuant to the order or requirement of a court; administrative agency,

 or other government body, provided Receiver takes all reasonable steps to keep the Confidential Information from becoming part of public records;
